= content_for :page_title_prefix, t("accessibility_statement.title")

%main.govuk-main-wrapper#main-content{ role: "main" }
  .govuk-grid-row
    .govuk-grid-column-two-thirds
      %h1.govuk-heading-xl
        = t("accessibility_statement.title")
      %p.govuk-body
        This accessibility statement applies to the report your official development assistance (ODA) service. The service is used by the Department for Business, Energy, and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) and its delivery partners to add and manage information about funds and related activities for official development assistance, report actual and forecast spend on activities, and show summaries of ODA activity.
      %p.govuk-body
        This service is managed by the Department for Business, Energy, and Industrial Strategy (BEIS). We want as many people as possible to be able to use this service. For example, that means you should be able to:
      %ul.govuk-list.govuk-list--bullet
        %li.govuk-list-item
          zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen
        %li.govuk-list-item
          navigate most of the service using just a keyboard
        %li.govuk-list-item
          navigate most of the service using speech recognition software
        %li.govuk-list-item
          listen to most of the service using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver)
      %p.govuk-body
        We’ve also made the service text as simple as possible to understand.
      %p.govuk-body
        = link_to_new_tab("AbilityNet", "https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/")
        has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability"

      %h2.govuk-heading-m
        What to do if you can’t access parts of this service
      %p.govuk-body
        If you need information for this service in a different format or cannot use the service and would like to report an accessibility problem, contact us at <a href="mailto:RODAsupport@odamanagement.org" class="govuk-link">RODAsupport@odamanagement.org</a>
      %p.govuk-body
        We’ll consider your request and get back to you in 5 days.
      %h2.govuk-heading-m
        Enforcement procedure
      %p.govuk-body
        The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the ‘accessibility regulations’). If you’re not happy with how we respond to your complaint,
        = link_to_new_tab("contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS)", "https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/")
      %h2.govuk-heading-m
        Technical information about this service’s accessibility
      %p.govuk-body
        The Department for Business, Energy, and Industrial Strategy is committed to making its services accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.
      %h3.govuk-heading-s
        Compliance status
      %p.govuk-body
        This service is fully compliant with the
        = link_to_new_tab("Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1", "https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/")
        AAA  standard.
      %p.govuk-body
        The service is being iterated and we will update this statement with details of any accessibility issues with new features.
      %h2.govuk-heading-m
        Preparation of this accessibility statement
      %p.govuk-body
        This statement was prepared on 17 June 2020. It was last reviewed on 18 June 2020.
      %p.govuk-body
        This service was last tested on 31 March 2020. The test was carried out by the
        = link_to_new_tab("Digital Accessibility Centre", "https://digitalaccessibilitycentre.org/")
      %p.govuk-body
        The service was assessed against the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines WCAG 2.1.

